<H3> <TI>   Czech Republic's Klaus Arrives To Boost Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Republic's Klaus Arrives To Boost Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904082994 Prague CTK in English 2344 GMT 18 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, April 19 (CTK) -- Czech Premier 
Vaclav Klaus arrived for an official visit to Argentina last 
night. 
  His Argentinian visit is the first on his ten-day trip 
around 
South America, which is to lead him also to Chile and Brazil. 
  At a briefing held after his arrival, Klaus told journalists 
that his trip was aimed to establish the best possible mutual 
contacts and find methods of the extension of mutual trade. The 
Czech Republic is open to the world and, like Argentina, 
fighting against all kinds of protectionism, Klaus said. 
  Argentinian Economic Minister Domingo Cavallo, at present 
also in charge of foreign affairs, who met Klaus at the airport, 
showed interest in the privatization process in the Czech 
Republic. 
  Later in the night, Klaus was to visit the prestigious 
Argentinian Committee for Foreign Relations, where he was to 
acquaint leading Argentinian politicians with the transformation 
process now underway in the Czech Republic, and with his 
country's integration into European political, security and 
economic structures. 
  During his three-day stay in Buenos Aires, Klaus is to hold 
talks with Cavallo and meet with Argentinian President Carlos 
Menem. He is to lecture at Buenos Aires' Belgrano University 
and meet with representatives of Argentinian financial, business 
and industrial circles. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

