<H3> <TI>   Robaina on Importance of Emigrants Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Robaina on Importance of Emigrants Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2104043494 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0159 GMT 21 Apr 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2104043494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 20 Apr (PL) -- The most important thing is 
the path that is opening up, Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina 
told Cuban television today, referring to the Conference on the 
Nation and Emigration aimed at normalizing relations with 
residents abroad. 
  The conference also intends to seek the way in which we all, 
in a responsible and civilized manner, with respect and mutual 
understanding, can discuss common issues henceforth, the 
minister told the evening television newscast, upon arriving 
from a successful tour of several South American countries. 
  According to the foreign relations minister, for a long time 
the emigre community has been used as an instrument against Cuba. 
  As the reality of Cuban residents abroad is expressed 
differently and as the reality of the country changes, steps are 
taken as a result of a new situation, demonstrating the audacity 
of our project and the country convoking it, Robaina added. 
  The foreign minister said conditions continue to be as 
abnormal as before; therefore, it cannot be asked that ties with 
emigrants be normal. 
  Once more Cuba, rising above these circumstances, is capable 
of finding a solution and its own subject in these times, 
Robaina asserted. 
  Some 200 guests from over 40 countries will participate, on 
their own behalf, in the meeting that will run from next Friday 
to Sunday in this capital. 

</TEXT>

