<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry `Sources': Castro in `Perfect Health' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry `Sources': Castro in `Perfect Health' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2004155794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1533 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2004155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 20 Apr (EFE) -- Official Cuban Foreign 
Ministry sources today denied to EFE that President Fidel Castro 
had suffered a stroke and said "he is in perfect health." 
  The sources also denied Castro had been admitted to "Cimex" 
Hospital in Havana for a checkup. 
  The sources said Castro is not scheduled to attend the 
meeting between the Cuban Government and Cubans living abroad 
that begins on Friday, but they added that he will attend the 
next National Assembly of the People's Government meeting 
scheduled for 1 May. 
  Although Fidel Castro has not been seen in public since 2 
April, when he met with Chinese Deputy Planning Minister Hao 
Jianxiu, other sources said the Cuban president presided, as 
usual, at Monday's Council of Ministers meeting. 

</TEXT>

