<H3> <TI>   Power Plant Maintenance Period To Be Reduced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Power Plant Maintenance Period To Be Reduced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2004220194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2004220194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the spirit of winning the electricity-generation 
battle, workers from the Antonio Maceo plant, formerly the Rente 
plant in Santiago de Cuba, are working hard to reduce the period 
required for maintenance. 
  The workers are curently working on repairing the boiler of 
the 100-megawatt Unit No. 4. The Rente plant [as heard] has six 
units capable of generating 500 megawatts an hour, but has this 
year been working at 40 percent of its capacity due to the delay 
in maintenance resulting from the national network situation and 
the lack of resources, which are now being received. 
  For this reason, Unit No. 4 is expected to be finished by 
June, and will continue operating with the other units to 
provide an acceptable response to the generation needs this year. 

</TEXT>

