<H3> <TI>   State Department Charged With Coup Complicity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Department Charged With Coup Complicity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2004173194 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2004173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Movement of Young Patriots [MOJEP] calls on the 
healthy forces of the country to stand in the way of the 
stateless persons. Those who staged the coup wanted to create a 
situation favorable to drug trafficking, according to statements 
by a MOJEP official. 
  [Begin unidentified MOJEP official recording, in Creole] 
Press declaration by MOJEP: We in the coordinating body of 
MOJEP call on the Haitian people to (?understand) why the 
Haitian Army and parliament staged the coup d'etat. (?The reason 
why) all phony political leaders, senators, and deputies of the 
State Department have plotted against democracy in order to 
crush the people is to maintain thieves, drug dealers, and 
zenglendos [pejorative for those who carry out tasks for the 
Macoutes] within the Army and crooked dealers in the parliament. 
This is due to the fact that the State Department knows that if 
President Jean-Bertrand Aristide returns to power, it will not 
be able to lead properly the drug trafficking in the country. 
In that sense, MOJEP calls on all militants, people's 
organizations, and staunch political parties that side with the 
people to throw their support behind President Aristide's battle 
so democracy can be established in the country. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

