<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Source Reports Transfers, Dismissals in Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Source Reports Transfers, Dismissals in Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2004172294 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2004172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A source close to the General Headquarters of the 
Haitian Armed Forces [FADH] points out that transfers have been 
carried out within the military institution. Thus, Lieutenant 
Colonel Erwin Mehu has been transferred from the General 
Headquarters to occupy the post of commander of the Croix-des- 
Bouquets garrison, replacing Col. Mondesir Beaubrun who has been 
transferred to the General Headquarters. The source pointed out 
that Warrant Officer Lamour of the fourth company and another 
sergeant of the same garrison have been dismissed from the FADH 
and will be handed over to the justice department very soon. By 
the way, the source dismissed reports of the death of Warrant 
Officer Lamour following possible physical abuse, saying that 
the warrant officer is just fine. 

</TEXT>

