<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: President Has Support of Military </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman: President Has Support of Military </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2004144994 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 1330 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2004144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Presidential spokesman Felix Loarca Guzman has said 
that the president of the Republic has the military corps' 
support, and he added that reports disseminated yesterday in the 
capital and in certain military zones are merely rumors. He 
also said the president spent yesterday conducting business as 
usual, as any president would, including attending some 
meetings. One of the meetings was with the boy who will be the 
poster child for this year's telethon. The president later met 
with the finance minister and then worked on a message he will 
address to the nation, possibly today, because he could not do 
it yesterday, given several priority commitments, Loarca Guzman 
emphasized. 

</TEXT>

