<H3> <TI>   Change 94's Carles Comments on Possible Front Against PRD </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Change 94's Carles Comments on Possible Front Against PRD </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2104014094 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2104014094 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Telemetro Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Ruben Dario Carles, presidential candidate for the 
Civic Renewal Party, Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement 
[MOLIRENA], and the National Renewal Movement [MORENA], also 
commented on the possibility of forming alliances. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Will there be 
sufficient political commitment to create the alliance MORENA 
and MOLIRENA have been calling for to establish a common front 
against the PRD [Democratic Revolutionary Party]? 
  [Carles] Everybody agrees on that. 
  [Reporter] Will Mr. Carles be willing to cede the head of 
the 
ticket to the Arnulfists, considering they are sticking to their 
stance? 
  [Carles] I do not want to talk about what others think. I am 
saying the country knows our ticket is the best, from an 
individual and collective standpoint. We have programs that are 
not novels, works of fiction, songs, or poems, but facts -- the 
result of our experience, knowledge, and capability. We have 
the best team. You will not find any of them on any video. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

