<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Planning Minister Says `Obscure Interests' Mar Image </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Planning Minister Says `Obscure Interests' Mar Image </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2104042294 Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA in Spanish 20 Apr 
94 p E-10 </F>

<F P=103> PA2104042294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Juan Manuel Diaz] </F>
  [Text] Planning and Economic Policy Minister Delia Cardenas 
said yesterday that obscure interests want to harm our 
international banking center and the Colon Free Zone and that 
some sectors of the U.S. Senate are attacking our country out of 
ignorance. 
  The minister also said that a survey of the participants was 
disclosed during the meeting [not further identified]. The 
survey revealed that Panama and Nicaragua are the countries with 
the worst economic growth forecasts. 
  The survey also showed that those surveyed pointed out that 
the political stability of a country is the main factor to take 
into account when investing abroad. 
  Cardenas underscored that during an Inter-American 
Development Bank (IDB) assembly, U.S. officials attacked 
Panamanian regulations for fighting money laundering and drug 
trafficking. She added that this is because of the lack of 
information on the country's measures against these two scourges. 
  The official pointed out that she defended herself from the 
constant attacks that some U.S. senators made during the 
meeting, because Panama's image abroad is not very clear. 

</TEXT>

