<H3> <TI>   Czech Prime Minister Signs Trade Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Prime Minister Signs Trade Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004120394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1000 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Presenter] Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus will 
today end his visit to Argentina and leave for Chile, the next 
stopover on his 10-day tour round Latin American countries. Our 
special correspondent in the prime minister's entourage, 
Miroslav Konvalina, reports from Buenos Aires. 
  [Konvalina] An agreement on cooperation between the 
ministries of foreign affairs of the Czech Republic and 
Argentina was signed in Buenos Aires on 19 April. Czech Prime 
Minister Vaclav Klaus and Domingo Cavallo, Argentinian minister 
of economy and public works and services, also signed a 
memorandum on the imminent conclusion of an agreement on a 
free-trade zone between our countries or even between the whole 
regions, including CEFTA [Central European Free Trade 
Association] in Central Europe and MERCOSUR [Common Market of 
the South] in Latin America. The memorandum obliges the two 
countries to finalize as soon as possible the agreements on the 
protection of investments and on the prevention of double 
taxation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

