<H3> <TI>   Salta City Teachers Demonstrate, Clash With Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salta City Teachers Demonstrate, Clash With Police </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2004212694 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1732 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2004212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Salta, 20 Apr (NA) -- Demonstrators and police 
clashed again today in the main plaza of the city of Salta when 
a provincial teachers demonstration degenerated into serious 
disturbances. 
  The disturbances took place in the plaza, where police 
chased 
and beat demonstrators, including an elderly lady who fell on 
her back. 
  As a consequence, four university students were arrested in 
the Casino de las Nubes, where they had sought refuge. 
  The Human Rights Commission was able to get the arrested 
students taken to the Medical Culture House and not to a police 
precinct. 
  This is yet another chapter of the very long struggle by the 
provincial teachers to obtain payment of money they are owed 
within the framework of a conflictive situation. 
  Some 2,000 provincial teachers participated in today's 
demonstration. They marched along demanding salary improvements. 
  Teachers from the provinces of Buenos Aires, Formosa, 
Cordoba, and Santa Fe participated in today's demonstration to 
show solidarity with their Salta colleagues. 

</TEXT>

