<H3> <TI>   Demonstration Continues; Strike Set </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demonstration Continues; Strike Set </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2004235394 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2154 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2004235394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] San Salvador de Jujuy, 20 Apr (NA) -- Some 2,000 
state workers participated today in a peaceful demonstration in 
front of the provincial Government House demanding better 
salaries. 
  The protest, the first one in the tenure of new Governor 
Oscar Perassi, was organized by the State Unions Front, whose 
main leader is Carlos "Perro" Santillan, the municipal workers' 
leader. 
  The workers, who are demanding that the 80-peso increase 
granted by the government be incorporated into their fringe 
benefits package and not be considered just a pay increase, were 
policed by a Border Guard unit because no policeman put in an 
appearance. 
  The labor leaders who put themselves at the head of the 
protesters indicated today that on 27 April they will carry out 
a general strike in the province if the government does not give 
a concrete answer to their demands. 
  Despite the fact that there were no incidents, the 
demonstration was held in an atmosphere of tension because the 
recent serious incidents in the beginning of the month still are 
on people's minds. [passage omitted] 

