<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Approves 3 Special Powers Act Decrees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Approves 3 Special Powers Act Decrees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2104025194 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2104025194 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cecilia Pachano from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Council of Ministers approved in its session 
this afternoon the three first decrees contemplated in the 
Special Powers Act. These decrees allowed the Council of 
Ministers to promulgate the Law on Bank Debits, Law on 
Concessions for Construction and Maintenance of Public Works, 
and Law on Reforms of the Public Budget Law. 
  Regarding the Law on Bank Debits, the only modification made 
to the original draft bill was that stock market operations will 
only be taxed for first operations and will maintain the 0.75 
percent profitability rate. This law will go into effect on 2 
May. The government hopes to collect 100 billion bolivares with 
its implementation. 
  Regarding the Law on Concessions for Construction and 
Maintenance of Public Works, it is estimated its passage will 
promote the construction of public works, benefiting the 
community which will receive these new works and the state, 
which will not disburse any money for their construction. 
  [Begin Guillermo Alvarez, Central Information Office 
minister, recording] The profit margins offered by the past law 
ranged from 40 to 45 percent of the investment, which was 
evidently not attractive for investors. Now we have placed the 
profit margin at 75 percent. It may even reach 90 percent 
eventually with the authorization of Congress. 
  This is very important because it permits us to undertake 
works the government would have otherwise been unable to take 
on. [end recording] 
  As was known previously, the Law on Reforms of the Public 
Budget Law only contemplates the modification in the 
presentation date, which for the first quarter of the year was 
moved to the first 15 days of the month of June. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

