<H3> <TI>   Joint Cooperation Agreement Signed With France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Cooperation Agreement Signed With France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2104033594 Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network in Spanish 
2300 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2104033594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Chilean Foreign Ministry reported that the 
French and Chilean Governments have signed a joint agreement on 
the protection of investments, which the Chilean Congress 
approved on 22 December 1992. 
  Roger Romani, minister delegate of relations with the 
Senate, 
noted the agreement's significance. He said that it represents 
an important change for Chilean international economic relations 
and an unusual agreement for France compared with those signed 
by any other Latin American countries. 
  Romani also commented on the new Chilean economic policy's 
guidelines during the Senate session in which the agreement was 
analyzed. He said: This economic policy "had significant 
results," such as controlled inflation, strong growth, and the 
renewed confidence of international financial organizations. 
  The Chilean Foreign Ministry also reported that (Andre 
Guaier), French defense and Armed Forces Foreign Affairs 
Committee coordinator, also pointed out the Chilean economy's 
success. Commenting on Chilean-French relations, (Guaier) said 
they are based on an active cooperation and development policy, 
a very open policy on credit guarantees, and the programming of 
investments through privileged financial cooperation. 

</TEXT>

