<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Louis Vianet, secretary general of the French 
General Confederation of Labor, arrived this afternoon in Cuba 
at the head of a high-ranking delegation. Upon his arrival at 
the Jose Marti International Airport, where he was met by Pedro 
Ross Leal, secretary general of the Cuban Workers Federation 
[CTC] and other officials of the Cuban labor union movement, 
Vianet stated: I bring the solidarity of the French workers to 
the Cuban labor union movement. The members of this high-level 
delegation from France will also participate in various 
ceremonies in Havana City to salute 1 May, and will visit 
centers of economic and social interest on the island. 
  It was also announced that so far, 389 delegates from 27 
countries have confirmed their participation in Cuba's central 
activities marking International Workers Day. These guests 
belong to 59 labor union organizations from different parts of 
the world. 

</TEXT>

