<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Reports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2104150594 </F>
<F P=103> PY2104150594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities monitored through 21 April. 
  The Labor Ministry reported today that during 1993, 
unemployment insurance was provided to five times more 
individuals than during the previous year. (Buenos Aires 
NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS 2048 GMT 19 Apr 94) 
  The Association of Motor Vehicle Manufacturers, ADEFA, 
reported today that the production of motor vehicles during 
March 1994 totalled 33,758 units, a 300 percent increase with 
respect to February of this year and a 30 percent increase with 
respect to March 1993. ADEFA also reported that total 
production during the first quarter of 1994 was 34 percent 
higher than during the first quarter of 1993, and that the total 
number of units exported during the period increased by 121 
percent with respect to the same period of last year. (Buenos 
Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 2315 GMT 14 Apr 94) 

</TEXT>

