<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows PRD Candidate Leading Field </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows PRD Candidate Leading Field </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2204010494 Panama City LA PRENSA in Spanish 21 Apr 94 p 2A </F>
<F P=103> PA2204010494 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA PRENSA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Orlando Mendieta C.] </F>
  [Text] Ernesto Perez Balladares, presidential candidate for 
the Democratic Revolutionary Party (PRD), has fallen 3.5 percent 
in voter preference for election as president of Panama, while 
Ruben Blades of the Papa Egoro Movement [MPE] moved up to second 
place, increasing his popularity among voters by 3.1 percent, 
according to a poll conducted by the Center for Latin American 
Studies (CELA). 
  Marco Gandasegui, director of the CELA survey, reported that 
the fifth CELA poll was conducted in early April among 2,600 
people, excluding the Provinces of Darien, Bocas del Toro, and 
the San Blas Intendancy. 
  According to Gandasegui, in light of the call to unite civic 
forces against the PRD, a virtual union between Carles, Mireya 
Moscoso de Gruber, and Eduardo Vallarino could garner a high 
enough percentage of votes to challenge the candidacy of Perez 
Balladares. 
  The poll revealed that Perez Balladares continues to lead 
voters' preferences with 29.7 percent. However, he descended in 
popularity in comparison with the previous CELA poll, in which 
he obtained 33.2 percent support. 
  Meanwhile, Blades, who in the previous poll got 13.4 
percent, 
which placed him third in voter preference, won 16.5 percent of 
popular support in this poll, boosting him into second place. 
  Although he registered a 0.4-percent increase in popular 
support over the previous poll, Ruben Dario Carles of MOLIRENA 
[Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement] has fallen back to 
third place on the chart with 14.8 percent support. 
  Meanwhile, Mireya Moscoso de Gruber of the Arnulfist Party 
came in fourth in voter preference with 14.3 percent, reflecting 
a 6.3-percent hike over the previous poll in which she won 8.5 
percent support. 
  The CELA poll revealed the following order for other 
candidates: Eduardo Vallarino of the Christian Democratic Party 
(PDC) with 2.6 percent, Samuel Lewis Galindo of Solidarity with 
1.3 percent, and Jose Salvador Munoz of the Doctrinaire 
Panamenist Party with 0.3 percent. 
  Gandasegui said that this was the last CELA poll before the 
8 
May elections. He announced that the organization plans to 
conduct another survey once the elections are over. 
  He added that this poll was conducted before President 
Endara 
aired the videos showing compromising footage against the PRD, 
as well as before the latest ILDEA-sponsored [Latin American 
Institute of Advanced Studies] presidential debate. Gandasegui 
noted that it is possible that these events have changed the 
level of preference for specific candidates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-11133 </DOCNO>
