<H3> <TI>   Council of State Honors French Politburo Member </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council of State Honors French Politburo Member </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2304172394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2304172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the instigation of the Cuban Workers Federation, 
CTC, the Council of State presented the Order of Lazaro Pena, 
First Degree, to Louis Vianet, secretary general of the General 
Confederation of Labor, CGT, and a member of the Politburo of 
the French Communist Party. As an expression of the 
acknowledgement by Cuba's workers and people of his 
contributions within the CGT toward friendship and solidarity 
with the Cuban Revolution, said Pedro Ross Leal, member of the 
Politburo of the Communist Party of Cuba and secretary general 
of the CTC, may this order be proof of our friendship and our 
respect. 
  This morning, Vianet and the delegation of French labor 
leaders accompanying him toured economic centers in Guines 
Municipality, Havana Province. At the Blas Roca Calderio UBPC 
[Basic Cooperative Production Unit], they donated 120,000 francs 
to the needs of Cuba's workers. With the check, they presented 
the CGT emblem, explaining that its two hands represent unity, 
also, in the French and Cuban workers' struggle against the 
Yankee blockade. 
  The delegation attended the ceremony on Lenin Hill in Regla 
Municipality, Havana City Province, on the occasion of the 
anniversary of Lenin's birth -- the first ceremony to be held in 
the city of Havana in commemoration of 1 May. 
  Vianet is at this moment holding a news conference on the 
situation of workers in France and on the international workers 
movement. 

</TEXT>

