<H3> <TI>   Council of State Endorses 7 New Ministries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council of State Endorses 7 New Ministries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2204115794 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1102 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2204115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of State's Decree Law 147, approved on 
21 April and endorsed [refrendado] by Comrade Fidel Castro, 
establishes a total of 27 ministries and five institutes to 
constitute henceforth the central administration of the state. 
The Council of State decree also creates ministries for new 
organizations or those experiencing name changes. 
  These new ministries and their respective ministers are: 
Rosa 
Elena Simeon Negrin, Ministry of Science, Technology, and the 
Environment; Antonio Rodriguez Maurell, Ministry of Economy and 
Planning; Jose Luis Rodriguez Garcia, Ministry of Finances and 
Prices; Ignacio Gonzalez Planas, Ministry of Metallurgy and 
Electronics Industry; Francisco Linares Calvo, Ministry of Labor 
and Social Security; Osmany Cienfuegos Gorriaran, Ministry of 
Tourism; and Ernesto Melendez Bachs, Ministry of Foreign 
Investment and Economic Cooperation. 
  Officials relieved because of the elimination of their 
organizations are: Sonia Rodriguez Cardona, minister president 
of the State Committee for Technical and Material Supply; Fidel 
Vascos Gonzalez, minister president of the State Committee for 
Statistics; Ramon Darias Rodes, minister president of the State 
Committee for Standardization; Arturo Guzman Pascual, minister 
president of the State Committee for Prices; Samuel Savariego 
Capuano, president of the National Automated Systems and 
Computing Technology Institute; and Rafael Sed Perez, president 
of the National Tourism Institute. 

</TEXT>

