<H3> <TI>   Speaks at Eastern Army Fish Farm Opening </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaks at Eastern Army Fish Farm Opening </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2304142394 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2304142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statements by Army General Raul Castro Ruz during the </F>
inauguration of the Eastern Army's fish farming center in Las 
Tunas Province; date not given -- recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] [Unidentified announcer] After 
hearing a detailed report by Colonel Jose Ramon Jimenez, head of 
the General Staff of the Defense Council in Las Tunas, on the 
characteristics of the project, Army General Raul Castro, 
minister of the Revolutionary Armed Forces, toured areas of the 
new installation. He was accompanied by Commander of the 
Revolution Juan Almeida Bosque and Division General Ramon 
Espinosa Martin, head of the Eastern Army. 
  After completing his tour of the facilities, the second 
secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of 
Cuba highlighted the significance of the development of fish 
farming in our country and its contribution to the nutrition of 
the people. 
  [Castro] On a water tank not far from here, there is a sign 
that reads: Under our conditions of the special period, beans 
are as valuable as cannon. This is a statement I once made and 
later rectified by saying: At this moment, beans are more 
valuable than cannon. Today, as many of you saw, I used a marker 
to add to the sign: and fish farming, which is the most 
inexpensive way of obtaining a magnificent source of protein for 
our people and our Armed Forces. I hope the Eastern Army, as in 
other activities, will be the vanguard in fish farming and in 
fraternal emulation among Army units. 
  [Unidentified announcer] Gen. Raul Castro once again took 
advantage of the opportunity to congratulate the Eastern Army on 
the occasion of its 33d anniversary. 
  [Castro] Here in Las Tunas, in this very regiment, and with 
the inauguration of this important fish farming center, on my 
behalf and on behalf of my companions Commander of the 
Revolution Juan Almeida Bosque, Ramon Espinosa, head of the 
Eastern Army, and of the commander in chief, once again I 
congratulate the Eastern Army. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

