<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Representative on Haitian Occupation Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNHCR Representative on Haitian Occupation Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2404173794 Paris AFP in Spanish 1623 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2404173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santo Domingo, 24 Apr (AFP) -- UNHCR representative 
Juan Manuel Castro, a Peruvian national, has said talks with the 
group of 102 Haitians who are occupying the offices of the UN 
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) in the Dominican Republic 
have been unsuccessful up to now. 
  The Haitians, 50 men, 20 women, and 32 children, occupied 
the 
UNHCR offices in downtown Santo Domingo on Friday to demand that 
they be granted refugee status. 
  Castro told the media that the talks "have been 
unsuccessful, 
and we do not know what their intentions are. F. Castro visited 
the Haitians who are occupying the UNHCR offices today and 
ordered they be given more food and medicine. 
  The Dominican police have had the block where the UNHCR 
offices are located surrounded since Friday, but there has been 
no official statement from the government of President Joaquin 
Balaguer. 

</TEXT>

