BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jaime Guerrero from the "Meridian" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Peace Commissioner Manuel Camacho Solis confirmed 
that the Zapatist National Liberation Army [EZLN] will continue 
its consultation process with the Indian communities before 
returning to the reconciliation dialogue. 
  Camacho Solis said that with the return of a portion of the 
EZLN troops to their communities, the tension in Chiapas will 
decrease and a clear course in favor of the resumption of the 
talks is marked. Thursday night, the EZLN Command reported that 
a portion of its members would return to their places of origin. 
Moreover, the EZLN will continue with its consultation process 
to return to the reconciliation dialogue. Camacho Solis said the 
EZLN is responding to the messages for peace made by the 
government and the civilian society. 
  [Begin Camacho Solis recording] I believe it is good news 
for 
the country to know the EZLN is responding to these actions with 
actions that set a very clear course in favor of the resumption 
of the talks. [end recording] 
  The peace commissioner met with President Carlos Salinas and 
with Chiapas Governor Javier Lopez at noon. Today, members of 
the State Committee of Indian and Peasant Organizations of 
Chiapas, who invaded lands in the state, agreed to contribute to 
the peace process in Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

