<H3> <TI>   Salinas Names Inquiry Commission Into Colosio Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salinas Names Inquiry Commission Into Colosio Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2204221994 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2204221994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Today, President Carlos Salinas de Gortari announced 
the creation of a commission of citizens, including some who are 
critical of or opposed to the government, to help investigate 
the murder of Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential candidate of 
the Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI]. In a brief 
statement made at the Vicente Guerrero Hall of the Los Pinos 
residence, the president noted that Mexico wants to know the 
truth. 
  [Begin Salinas recording] At the same time, it is necessary 
to avoid a climate of mutual suspicion. Any inquiry is 
difficult; it takes time. We cannot, however, accept the 
fostering of a climate of doubt. We are determined to open the 
investigation so that citizens of the highest professional 
quality can participate. [end recording] 
  The commission will comprise the following people: Carlos 
Payan, newsman and LA JORNADA daily editor; (Fernando Gomez 
Montt), National Action Party federal deputy and chairman of the 
Chamber of Deputies Justice Committee; Leonel Godoy, former 
Michoacan State attorney general, former deputy of the Party of 
the Democratic Revolution, and special prosecutor in the Obando 
and Hill case; lawyer (Agustin Santamarina); and Agustin Basabe, 
PRI deputy for Nuevo Leon State and former Colosio adviser. The 
president thanked these citizens for their willingness to 
participate in the task, which he described as delicate. He 
added that the Colosio Riojas family welcomes their 
participation. 

</TEXT>

