<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Diego Fernandez de Cevallos, National Action Party 
[PAN] candidate for president, has ruled out the possibility 
that an alliance of all the opposition forces in Mexico can 
defeat the Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI] in the coming 
August elections. Nevertheless, he said alliances could work 
under certain circumstances to advance democracy and defend the 
vote. 
  [Begin Fernandez recording] We can and should work with any 
political party to advance democracy. [end recording] 
  During a news conference held at the foreign correspondents 
section, Fernandez said there are two basic requirements for 
holding pure, credible elections. First, the PRI should lower 
its publicity expenses to keep them within legal limitations. 
Second, the media should allocate time to candidates equitably 
and serve the truth honestly. 

</TEXT>

