<H3> <TI>   Navy Rescues Cuban Boaters in Quintana Roo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Rescues Cuban Boaters in Quintana Roo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2404193894 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2154 GMT 22 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2404193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Chetumal, Mexico, 22 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- The Mexican 
Navy rescued 94 Cubans after the Cubans' boat, which had drifted 
for several days, ran aground on the Banco Chinchorro reef area 
in southern Quintana Roo State. 
  Roberto Erales Jimenez, under secretary of the state 
government, said the group, composed of 47 men, 27 women, and 20 
children, sailed from Puerto Tuna, Cuba, on 15 April aboard the 
30-foot boat "Casilda 27." 
  Governor Mario Villanueva Madrid reported that the Cubans 
were rescued by Navy members, who helped them get to the village 
of Mahahual, some 45 km east of Chetumal, where they were given 
medical assistance and food. The governor said the Mexican 
immigration authorities issued them a permit to stay on Mexican 
territory until next Sunday. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

