<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Education Official Dies from Heart Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuban Education Official Dies from Heart Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2404011094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2112 GMT 23 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2404011094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 23 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Embassy 
in Mexico has reported that Alfredo Alfonso Guillin Zelaya, an 
official of the Cuban Education Ministry, died of a heart attack 
during a working visit to Chihuahua State in northern Mexico. 
  Guillin, who was of Mexican origin, died at the age of 57 on 
Friday and his remains will be transferred to Cuba, the embassy 
reported in a communique in which they stated they had sent 
their condolences to relatives in Cuba and Mexico. 
  Guillin had come to Mexico two weeks ago at the head of a 
three-member delegation from the Cuban Education Ministry. "The 
official was due to return to Cuba today (Saturday) at the end 
of his mission," an embassy spokesman said. 
  Guillin was 19 years old in December 1956 when he embarked 
on 
an expedition aboard a yacht that departed from the Mexican port 
of Tuxpan, Veracruz State, bound for Cuba to begin an armed 
struggle that ended in January 1959 with the rebel triumph. The 
expedition was led by Cuban President Fidel Castro. 

</TEXT>

