<H3> <TI>   TSE Reports Polls Closed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TSE Reports Polls Closed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2504001894 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2306 GMT 24 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2504001894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador, 24 Apr (NOTIMEX) -- The Salvadoran 
presidential elections ended at 1700 local (2300 GMT) today, the 
Supreme Electoral Tribunal [TSE] reported. 
  The elections, which began at 0700 (1300 GMT), were 
characterized by voter apathy and low turnout, the extent of 
which has not yet been estimated. 
  The TSE called upon all 2.7 million citizens eligible to 
vote 
to do so and installed 381 voting centers in 262 municipalities 
throughout the entire country. 
  Once the polling stations closed, the TSE immediately began 
receiving the vote count certificates at the official vote 
counting center located in a luxury hotel in San Salvador. 
  The TSE authorities announced this afternoon that the first 
preliminary report will be announced after 30 percent of the 
votes cast are counted. 

</TEXT>

