<H3> <TI>   Cristiani Announces `New President' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cristiani Announces `New President' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2504024294 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSKL in Spanish 0154 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2504024294 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Radio Cadena YSKL </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Part" of news conference by President Alfredo Cristiani </F>
with unidentified reporters at the Supreme Electoral Tribunal 
headquarters at the Hotel Presidente in San Salvador -- live] 
  [Text] [Cristiani] I think we can eliminate the word 
possible from the results as we have sufficient evidence of the 
voting trend. We have a new president and vice president. We 
are very pleased, particularly about the way in which the 
Salvadoran people once again expressed their feelings 
peacefully. We hope that from now on the country will be able 
to do everything that is required. The political campaign is 
over. I will continue working for the benefit of the Salvadoran 
people. 
  [Unidentified reporter] What about the people not (?liking) 
the Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front [FMLN] [words 
indistinct]? 
  [Cristiani] We must not necessarily view it as the people 
either liking or disliking the FMLN. The people simply 
preferred another political force. We must realize that there 
are always some people who receive more votes than others and 
[words indistinct]. 
  [Reporter] [Words indistinct] 
  [Cristiani] We have had reports of some irregularities. 
Generally speaking, everything went very well. There was one 
incident in Pasaquina, but we do not have the details. We will 
have to check that out, but I do not think it will affect the 
elections. 

</TEXT>

