<H3> <TI>   Colorado Party Deputy Gunned Down in Ciudad del Este </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colorado Party Deputy Gunned Down in Ciudad del Este </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2404012094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2310 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2404012094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asuncion, 23 Apr (EFE) -- The National Police 
reported that a Paraguayan department deputy belonging to the 
ruling National Republican Association (Colorado Party) was shot 
to death today, Saturday. 
  The incident took place in Ciudad del Este, 320 km from 
Asuncion. The victim was identified as Julio Cesar Riquelme, 
national deputy for Alto Parana Department, who died of several 
gunshot wounds. Two other persons were wounded in the incident 
and were taken to a hospital in Ciudad del Este, capital of Alto 
Parana Department on the Brazilian border. 
  Police arrested Tomas Lezcano, 39 years old, as the alleged 
killer but gave no further details on the case. 

</TEXT>

